documentation.text:
A Perceptron where the data given for updating and predicting is sparse.
`update` and `predict` methods take `data` that holds the indices of the features that are present.

typeDescriptions.typeString: literal_string "A feature index is too large."

arguments.value: A feature index is too large.

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "A feature index is too large."

documentation.text:
Initialize sparse weights for the model.
Made to be called just after the contract is created and never again.
@param _weights A sparse representation of the weights.
Each innermost array is a tuple of the feature index and the weight for that feature.

Evaluate a batch.
     * Force samples to have a size of 60 because about 78% of the IMDB test data has less than 60 tokens. If the sample has less than 60 unique tokens, then use a value > weights.length.
     * @return numCorrect The number correct in the batch.

attributes.text:
Evaluate a batch.
     * Force samples to have a size of 60 because about 78% of the IMDB test data has less than 60 tokens. If the sample has less than 60 unique tokens, then use a value > weights.length.
     * @return numCorrect The number correct in the batch.

params._featureIndices: The feature indices to append to the array held by this contract.

params._classifications: The classifications supported by the model.
params._intercept: The bias to add to the multiplication of the weights and the data. Multiplied by `toFloat`.
params._learningRate: (Optional, defaults to 1). The amount of impact that new training data has to the weights. Multiplied by `toFloat`.
params._weights: The weights for the model. Each multiplied by `toFloat`.

returns.numCorrect: The number correct in the batch.

returns._0: The number of possible classifications that can be predicted.
The number of feature indices to use. 0 means to use all feature from the encoding.

params._weights: A sparse representation of the weights. Each innermost array is a tuple of the feature index and the weight for that feature.
The weights to set for the model.
params.startIndex: The index to start placing `_weights` into the model's weights.

addFeatureIndices(uint32[]).notice: Add more feature indices to take from the encoded result. Made to be called just after the contract is created and never again.

evaluateBatch(uint24[60][],uint64[]).notice: Evaluate a batch.     * Force samples to have a size of 60 because about 78% of the IMDB test data has less than 60 tokens. If the sample has less than 60 unique tokens, then use a value > weights.length.

initializeSparseWeights(int80[][]).notice: Initialize sparse weights for the model. Made to be called just after the contract is created and never again.

initializeWeights(uint64,int80[]).notice: Initialize weights for the model. Made to be called just after the contract is created and never again.
